Due to the local success of their independent debut release of "Mood Indigo", they landed a recording contract with RCA Records and sold half a million copies of the recording, and were voted Most Promising Instrumental Group of 1954 by Cashbox magazine.
In 1957, their song "Almost Paradise" hit number 18, and Petty won his first BMI writers' award.
Despite the success of his own records, Petty began construction of his Clovis studio in late 1954.

Also, the hits "Sugar Shack" and "Bottle of Wine" by Jimmy Gilmer and the Fireballs and "Wheels" by the String-A-Longs were recorded at Petty's studio in the 1960s.
Petty served as Buddy Holly's producer and also as his first manager until late 1958.
Petty purchased the Mesa Theater on Main Street in Clovis in 1960.

In 1963, he launched the FM radio station KTQM starting as an easy-listening station, later switching to country-and-western music, and then in 1968 to top-40 rock.
The country genre had local appeal, so he applied for a new station license and started KWKA 680 AM in 1971, airing country-and-western music.
Petty ran both stations until 1979.
The stations were sold by Curry County Broadcasting to Zia Broadcasting in 2010.
Petty died in Lubbock, Texas, in August 1984, of leukemia.
Later in 1984, he was posthumously named Clovis Citizen of the Year.
His wife, Vi, died in March 1992.
She helped start the "Norman and Vi Petty Music Festival" in Clovis in 1987, which ran until 1997.

sentences: Norman Petty (May 25, 1927 – August 15, 1984) was an American musician and record producer who is best known for recording Buddy Holly and the Crickets in his studio.

Throughout the 1950s and 1960s, recordings produced by Petty, in various musical styles, were issued by virtually every major record label in the United States and Canada, with numerous regional successes.
The country genre had local appeal, so he applied for a new station license and started KWKA 680 AM in 1971, airing country-and-western music.
Later in 1984, he was posthumously named Clovis Citizen of the Year.

Norman and Vi were given awards for "Outstanding Graduate Accomplishment" (in the classes of 1945 and 1946, respectively) by the Clovis Municipal Schools Foundation and Alumni Association in April 2011.

The awards are presented to Clovis High School graduates for achievement in their sphere of business; the recipients are chosen because their strength of character and citizenship, to serve as models for today's CHS students.

Petty's Nor-Va-Jak record label was revived in 2016 as "Nor-Va-Jak Music", with authorization from Norman Petty Studios, for the purpose of reissuing Petty productions that were not previously available on CD.
Previously, many Petty productions had been issued in the UK by both Ace Records and Rollercoaster Records.
